cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL

The paper proposes a framework for improving classification performance on imbalanced data using deep learning models, specifically convolutional neural networks (CNNs). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) since CNNs are commonly used in image classification tasks. The paper also involves supervised representation learning, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the iterative process of training the CNN and updating the targets involves optimization techniques, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses public benchmarks to evaluate the proposed framework, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
